ove.";i:42;s:68:"Replace your chaindriven garage door opener using a beltdriven type.";i:43;s:58:"Change out your steel rollers with more quiet rubber ones.";i:44;s:61:"Change out your extension spring system with torsion springs.";i:45;s:89:"One common complaint by homeowners is that their garage door opener makes too much noise.";i:46;s:89:"While it is not possible to have a truly silent opener some are much quieter than others.";i:47;s:166:"Of the 3 main types of opener belt chain and screw belt drives are purported to be the quietest with screw drives a close second and chain drives pulling up the rear.";i:48;s:29:"Steps you can do on your own.";i:49;s:156:"Safety first Before you begin ensure that the area is well lit and that there is no objects lying around the place as you operate your step ladder or stool.";i:50;s:114:"Disconnect the garage door from its power source to prevent anyone attempting to open it as you are working on it.";i:51;s:133:"A loud garage door opener that makes a lot of noise is for some people a slight nuisance and for others a reason to wake up at night.";i:52;s:47:"Some garage door motors are louder than others.";i:53;s:76:"Noise levels depend mostly on drive-style gear assembly and operating speed.";i:54;s:74:"Punch angle gauge door balance proper maintenance and correct install can.";i:55;s:98:"Garage door manufacturers and contractors have tips to keep your garage door from being obnoxious.";i:56;s:58:"Garage doors create vibrations during opening and closing.";i:57;s:44:"This results in loud and distracting noises.";i:58;s:41:"It might not be a problem during the day.";i:59;s:153:"We have the skills and years of experience in servicing and fixing garage doors in the Perth area and no job is too big or too small for us to deal with.";i:60;s:82:"If you need help with your noisy garage door give us a call today on 08 6161 5665.";i:61;s:113:"Your garage door may also be noisy because the insulation strip on the bottom of the door is worn out or missing.";i:62;s:137:"With a missing insulation strip you will feel cold and wet coming into your garage and hear a loud banging noise when the door is closed.";i:63;s:78:"Noise can also be caused by the garage door hitting the cement floor too hard.";i:64;s:39:"How to Stop a Noisy Garage Door Opener.";i:65;s:82:"Vibration is the cause of most noise problems associated with garage door openers.";i:66;s:66:"Vibration transfers through the steel framework of the opener and.";i:67;s:89:"Worn gears inside the garage door openers motor unit can make grinding or buzzing noises.";i:68;s:102:"Replace the gear and sprocket assembly or the drive and worm gears when theyre worn and making noises.";i:69;s:114:"A worn belt or chain and cable assembly can also make noise-tighten chain or belt tension to correct this problem.";}}